HEADWORD: napa
<hw>napa</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A plant (<spn>Brassica rapa</spn>
<varn>pekinensis</varn>) with an elongated celerylike head of
broadstalked leaves used as a vegetable in east Asia; called also
<altname>Chinese cabbage</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Chinese cabbage, celery cabbage, pe-tsai,
<spn>Brassica rapa</spn> pekinensis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Napaea</ent>⟦br⟧
